---
description: Python and TDD conventions for src/ and tests/
globs: src/**/*.py,tests/**/*.py
---

- Target Python 3.12. Type-hint everything (`mypy --strict` must pass).
- Lint/format with ruff per `pyproject.toml`. Keep functions small and pure
  where possible — pure logic (parsing, categorization, dedup, scoring) gets
  unit tests; I/O paths get integration tests against the test Docker stack.
- TDD order: write the failing test first, then implement to green. Don't add
  code without a test. New module ⇒ new test module mirroring the path.
- CLIs use Click. Config/secrets come from env, never hard-coded.
- External calls (DeepSeek/OpenAI-compatible, Neo4j, Postgres) are mocked in
  unit tests (respx for HTTP); only e2e/integration tests hit real services.
- Cross-platform: use `pathlib`, not string paths or shell-isms.
